<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-04-08T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-04-08T19:00:00-05:00" n="238" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d238">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1173: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Special Representative of the President</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                            José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-04-08T18:00:00-06:00">April 8, 1938—6
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9:31 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>65. Complete and friendly accord on a recess for 2 months was
                                obtained and an act suspending plenary sessions to give ample time
                                for necessary studies was signed at 4 p.m. this afternoon by both
                                delegations and the members of the Mediation Commission. Press
                                informed. Travel authorization requested.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>